<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-04-12T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-04-12T16:00:00-05:00" n="323" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d323">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/3729</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister in Panama</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWJ1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Price</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-12T16:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 12, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your April 7, 10 p.m. Inform Government of Panama that action of
                                President in issuing proclamation of cooperation with the United
                                States against any hostile acts in Panama affecting this Government
                                is viewed with great satisfaction. You may say further that the
                                President has expressed his personal gratification at this
                                spontaneous action on the part of Panama in allying itself with the
                                Government of the United States in the protection of independence
                                and justice for the Americas and accepts this action as an
                                additional token of the steadfast friendship already existing
                                between our two Republics.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>